+{"id":"bd-1jv2y","title":"Audit Log Query Builder","description":"## Overview

Visual query construction for audit log searches with saved queries and export. Makes audit log exploration accessible to non-technical users and enables compliance workflows.

## Background & Justification

The audit.ts system captures comprehensive logs. But:
- Querying requires manual SQL/API knowledge
- No saved queries for recurring reports
- Export is manual
- Compliance teams need self-service

Query builder enables:
- Point-and-click query construction
- Saved queries for recurring needs
- Scheduled reports
- Export in multiple formats

## Key Components

### 1. Query Data Model

```typescript
interface AuditQuery {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description?: string;

  // Query definition
  filters: QueryFilter[];
  timeRange: { start: Date; end: Date } | { relative: string };
  groupBy?: string[];
  orderBy?: { field: string; direction: 'asc' | 'desc' };
  limit?: number;

  // Saved query metadata
  savedBy?: string;
  savedAt?: Date;
  isPublic?: boolean;
  schedule?: QuerySchedule;
}

interface QueryFilter {
  field: string;
  operator: 'eq' | 'neq' | 'contains' | 'startsWith' | 'in' | 'notIn' | 'gt' | 'lt' | 'between';
  value: any;
  conjunction: 'AND' | 'OR';
}

interface QuerySchedule {
  frequency: 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly';
  time: string; // HH:MM
  dayOfWeek?: number; // For weekly
  dayOfMonth?: number; // For monthly
  exportFormat: 'csv' | 'json' | 'pdf';
  recipients: string[];
}
```

### 2. UI Components

**Filter Builder:**
- Add filter row
- Field dropdown (auto-complete from schema)
- Operator dropdown
- Value input (type-aware)
- AND/OR toggle
- Remove filter

**Time Range Picker:**
- Relative presets (last hour, day, week, month)
- Custom date range
- Quick buttons

**Results Table:**
- Sortable columns
- Expandable rows for details
- Pagination
- Column visibility toggle

**Query Actions:**
- Run query
- Save query
- Export results
- Schedule query

### 3. Export Formats

**CSV:**
- Column headers
- Flattened nested objects
- Configurable columns

**JSON:**
- Full structure
- Pretty printed option
- NDJSON for streaming

**PDF:**
- Formatted report
- Logo/branding
- Summary statistics

### 4. Saved Queries

**My Queries:**
- Personal saved queries
- Edit/delete
- Clone

**Shared Queries:**
- Public queries from team
- View-only for non-owners

**Scheduled:**
- Active schedules
- Execution history
- Enable/disable

### 5. API Endpoints

- `POST /api/audit/query` - Execute query
- `GET /api/audit/saved-queries` - List saved queries
- `POST /api/audit/saved-queries` - Save query
- `PUT /api/audit/saved-queries/:id` - Update saved query
- `DELETE /api/audit/saved-queries/:id` - Delete saved query
- `POST /api/audit/export` - Export results
- `GET /api/audit/schema` - Available fields and types

## Database Schema

```sql
CREATE TABLE saved_audit_queries (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  query_definition TEXT NOT NULL, -- JSON
  saved_by TEXT NOT NULL,
  is_public INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  schedule TEXT, -- JSON
  created_at TEXT,
  updated_at TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE query_executions (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  query_id TEXT,
  executed_by TEXT,
  result_count INTEGER,
  execution_time_ms INTEGER,
  executed_at TEXT
);
```

## Implementation Tasks

1. Design query data model
2. Implement query execution engine
3. Build filter builder UI component
4. Build time range picker
5. Build results table with pagination
6. Implement export in all formats
7. Create saved query system
8. Implement query scheduling
9. Build saved queries management UI
10. Add API routes
11. Write unit tests for query engine
12. Write E2E test for query flow

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Filters can be added/removed dynamically
- [ ] All operators work correctly
- [ ] Results display in paginated table
- [ ] Export produces valid files
- [ ] Saved queries persist and reload
- [ ] Scheduled queries execute on time
- [ ] Shared queries visible to team

